caption: b'Our partners @renaultf1team are experts at applying data insights to gain a competitive edge at every race. We apply the same logic to global supply chains, learning and actioning in real-time to optimise our performance. The key to success is having full visibility over our cargo every step of the way. \n\nWith special appearances from @danielricciardo and @fernandoalo_oficial, watch how we deployed our latest container tracking technology to follow the journey of a Renault F1 car as DP World shipped it to the track.'

b"Dubai has made incredible progress over the last 60 years. From humble beginnings in pearling and fishing, to the modern epicentre of world trade, Dubai has a hand in growing economic prosperity for all those who do business there. Find out more about Dubai's opportunities at the link in our bio. 
 

#TradeReimagined #UAENationalDay #DubaiTrade"

b'Everyone loves a bargain - and on Black Friday it is usually consumers who are on the hunt for the best deal. But as any smart retailer will know, by streamlining supply chains and digitising management systems, they themselves can enjoy cost savings that eclipse any eye-catching deal - and all through the year. Visit the link in our bio to find out more. \n\n#TradeReimagined #BlackFriday'

b'Amid all the hustle and bustle on the quayside, this evening shot from the Port of Yuzhny shows that only a stones throw away, you can find moments of total calm.\n \n #Yuzhny #Ukraine #ContainerTerminal #SmartTrade'

b"Gain skills. Spark ambition. Think globally.
 
One of the best things about DP World's Global Education Programme is that it aims to help each child see how their nearest terminals can be a gateway to the world - just like these students are discovering at Callao, Peru. 
 
 #IEW #Education #DPWorldCallao"

b'This week, @virginhyperloop successfully completed the first test of human travel in a hyperloop pod. Our Chairman, and the Chairman of Virgin Hyperloop, Sultan Ahmed Bin Sulayem, was on-site to discuss its historical significance and note how it will transform human and cargo transportation. \n\n#Cargospeed #Hyperloop #FutureofTransportation #SmartTrade'

b"In a world first, passengers have successfully travelled via Hyperloop technology at the @VirginHyperloop test track in Nevada, USA. It's an exciting milestone for a technology that will propel mobility and logistics into the future at warp speed.\n\n#Cargospeed #Hyperloop #FutureofTransportation #SmartTrade"

b'Industrial symmetry: while everything at #DPWorldSouthampton is stacked and precisely ordered for efficiency, it also makes for some great insta-worthy shots! \n\n#Southampton #ContainerTerminal #SmartTrade'
b'Congratulations to @renaultF1team for their second podium of the season at the #ImolaGP.\n\n#RenaultDPWorldF1Team #DanielRicciardo #Renault #DPWorld #F1 #DR3'

b'Regram: This striking image was taken by helicopter and drone photographer @imagensaereas above our terminal in Santos, Brazil. Strategically located with access by sea, road and rail, the project has an annual movement capacity of 1.2 million TEUs - which the ships in this photo will help to transport.
 

 #SmartTrade #Santos #Brazil #ContainerTerminal'

b'DP World Yarimca is Turkey\xe2\x80\x99s most advanced container terminal. We employ the latest technology, including automation and blockchain solutions, to ensure the 1.3 million containers that move through Yarimca do so seamlessly. Our technology is creating new jobs in the region, including centralised planning and equipment control roles, to create supply chain efficiencies and enhance the Turkish economy. 

 
 #SmartTrade #Yarimca #Turkey #ContainerTerminal'

Our technology is creating new jobs in the region, including centralised planning and equipment control roles, to create supply chain efficiencies and enhance the Turkish economy.

b'Regram: This photo was originally posted by Instagram user @maritimegeek. It shows the CMA CGM Jean Mermoz alongside berth SCT5 shortly before her departure from our Southampton terminal. Carrying upwards of 20,000 containers, she is among the biggest container ships in the world. 

 
 #SmartTrade #ContainerTerminal #Southampton'

b'What can we do to restore the balance between people and our planet? Experts from all around the world will discuss solutions that will have measurable impact during the virtual Climate and Biodiversity Week by @expo2020dubai - in partnership with DP World. A sustainable future isn\xe2\x80\x99t out of reach. With resolve and global dialogue, we can achieve it. \n\n#Expo2020 #Biodiversity'

b'You have to be up close to appreciate the scale!\n \nThis week the first 6 towers for the \xe2\x80\x9cLa Estrella\xe2\x80\x9d wind turbine project arrived at @dpworld.sanantonio highlighting our multi-purpose terminal capabilities. Each blade has an average length of 71 meters and will soon form a group of 11 turbines approx. 100kms south of our terminal \xe2\x80\x93 generating, clean #sustainable energy from the power of the wind. :dashing_away::leaf_fluttering_in_wind::high_voltage:'

b'As the Global Logistics Partner of the @royalchallengersbangalore, it was up to us to transport the team\xe2\x80\x99s jerseys from India to Dubai for this year\xe2\x80\x99s tournament. Here\xe2\x80\x99s how we delivered the kit to where it needed to be, on time, all the way from factory to field.\n\nClick link in bio to find out more.'

b"DP World\xe2\x80\x99s Prince Rupert terminal is a one of a kind location, combining mountain views with North America's deepest natural harbour. It is strategically situated on the great circle route from Asia, which means our customers benefit from the fastest connection between Asian and North American markets on the planet. 
 

#SmartTrade #PrinceRupert #Canada #MountainViews"
b'Congratulations to @renaultf1team for a podium finish at the #EifelGP.\n\n#RenaultDPWorldF1Team @DanielRicciardo #Renault #DPWorld #F1 #DR3'

b'We proud to announce that DP World and @expo2020dubai are a Global Alliance Founding Partner of The @EarthshotPrize \xe2\x80\x93 the most prestigious global environment prize in history, launched today by HRH Prince William. Sharing ideas is part of our culture, and we look forward to seeking solutions that will improve the environmental health of the planet. To learn more, click the link in our bio.'

b'Young cricket fans around the world aspire to play like their role models, with dreams of competing on the big stage. We are proud to be the Global Logistics Partner of the @royalchallengersbangalore, a team that fuels people\xe2\x80\x99s love for the game and inspires young cricketers to take to the field.'

b"Our planet is a precious resource that we're fighting to protect, day-in-day out. Sustainable shipping is one way that we can work together to ensure our futures are peaceful and prosperous. Which is why we are proud to support the @UnitedNations Sustainable Development Goals on World Maritime Day 2020. \n\n#OurWorldOurFuture #WorldMaritimeDay #Sustainability #SustainableDevelopmentGoals #UnitedNations"

b'Great partnerships are the bedrock of great achievements. We are delighted to welcome the @royalchallengersbangalore to the DP World family and wish them all the best in this year\xe2\x80\x99s IPL.\n\n#IPL2020 #WeAreChallengers #Cricket @renaultf1team'

b'How do we tell one container apart from another? More importantly, how can we help you keep track of yours? \n\nWith Fr8manager by P&O Ferrymasters, you can pinpoint the exact location of your cargo in real time, over road, rail and sea, giving unbeatable visibility over your supply chain.'

b'Whether it\xe2\x80\x99s sport or business, you can\xe2\x80\x99t succeed without great leadership and strong partnerships. @RoyalChallengersBangalore share the same philosophy as us and it\xe2\x80\x99s one of the many reasons why we are proud to be their Global Logistics Partner. Click the link in our bio. #TogetherWeChallenge #WeAreChallengers #T20 #IPL2020 #Logistics #Cricket \xe2\x81\xa0'

b"Next time you indulge in a square of chocolate, consider the journey it takes for cocoa to go from bean to bar. Modern supply chains are just one of the reasons we're able to buy the treats we all like to enjoy. Tap the link in our bio to learn more. \n\n#Chocolate #SupplyChain #SmartTrade #TradeReimagined"

b"We're delighted to announce that we're the Global Logistics Partner for the @royalchallengersbangalore at this year's T20 tournament, taking place on our doorstep here in the UAE. Read more about our partnership - link in bio. \n#WeAreChallengers #Cricket #Bangalore #Logistics #SmartTrade #T20"

b'Regram: This overhead shot was first posted by Instagram user @maritimesouth. It shows our cargo handling capabilities in operation at DP World Lirqu\xc3\xa9n, Chile. Already the most developed economy in Latin America, Puerto Lirqu\xc3\xa9n contributes to Chile\xe2\x80\x99s attractive prospects for growth and dynamic business environment.\n\n#SmartTrade #Chile #Lirquen #PuertoLirquen'

b"Hurricanes. Typhoons. Cyclones. Their names differ depending on where you live in the world, but their impacts are equally fierce. Intelligent supply chains can help vessels move out of harm's way while at sea, and mobilise relief when these monsters take aim at land.\n\n#SmartTrade #Maritime #MaritimeIndustry #SupplyChain"

b'Regram: This gorgeous sunrise shot was taken by Instagram user @sydneytugboat at our Sydney terminal. Located in Botany Bay, the terminal provides a full range of electronic business support to clients, including electronic customs release of cargo, electronic data interchange reporting and web-browser-based information services.\n \n #SmartTrade #Sydney #BotanyBay #Australia'

b'Yuzhniy in the local language means "south" - which is apt given our Port of Yuzhniy\'s location in Ukraine. While winters may still be cold, summer evenings on the Black Sea coast are almost magical.\n \n #SmartTrade #BlackSea #Ukraine'

b"We may be physically apart, but we are together in our voices and actions as we adapt to the new normal. Here's our integrated response to #COVID19, brought to you from our employees around the world."

b'Regram: This image was originally shared by our colleagues at @dpworld_yarimca. It shows two new dock cranes in transport, on their way to our port in Turkey. These new cranes will dramatically speed up movement through the port, meaning your business can trade smarter, faster.\n\n#SmartTrade #Yarimca #Turkey'

#SmartTrade #Vancouver #Canada'

b'Golf is back in business! Following COVID-19 delays, the @EuropeanTour\xe2\x80\x99s 2020 season resumes today in the United Kingdom. The season-ending @dpwtc will take place from December 10-13 at Jumeirah Golf Estates, ensuring that our safety protocols meet international government guidance as it evolves. 

Keep up with all the action between now and December at the link in our bio. 

#EuropeanTour #Golf #RaceToDubai'

b'As we prepare for @Expo2020Dubai, we are focused on connecting minds to create a better future. 

The themes of opportunity, sustainability, mobility and innovation will come together at the DP World pavilion, demonstrating how can use future trade technologies to improve life for people and communities across the globe.

#PowerOfFlow #Expo2020 #Dubai'

b'Regram: This stunning shot was taken by one of our employees, @andrew.bowen. It shows the world\xe2\x80\x99s largest container vessel, HMM Algeciras, berthing at our port. Fully loaded and ready to go, it can carry up to 24,000 containers.\n\n#SmartTrade #London #LondonGateway'

b'Renault DP World F1 team announces Fernando Alonso will join Esteban Ocon in the driver line up for the 2021 season. We\xe2\x80\x99re delighted at the announcement of an F1 legend joining the team. It\xe2\x80\x99s yet another exciting step forward in the partnership. Welcome @fernandoalo_oficial \n\n#F1 #Formula1 #RenaultF1 #RenaultF1Team'

b'We are gearing up to shape a bright new future for all at @Expo2020Dubai. Watch our latest time lapse footage, as the DP World pavilion comes together on the Expo site. 

We are excited to showcase how we are keeping trade flowing, and together we will create a better future.

#PowerOfFlow #Expo2020 #Dubai'

b'Land, sea or rail isn\xe2\x80\x99t an issue for cargo passing through our terminal in Santos, Brazil. With its strategic location, DP World Santos has an annual container movement capacity of 1.2 million TEUs.\n\n#SmartTrade #Connectivity #Santos #Brazil'

b'Incredible changes have taken place for businesses in 2020, and for retailers this requires a comprehensive retooling of their supply chains. From personalised e-commerce, to Cargospeed with @virginhyperloop, click the link in our bio to learn more about the future of global trade.\n\n#TradeReimagined #SmartTrade #SupplyChain #Technology'

b'According to @WorldDesignOrg, "Industrial Design is a strategic problem-solving process that drives innovation, builds business success, and leads to a better quality of life." With views like this at Pusan Newport International Terminal, we think it can also be beautiful. \n#WIDD2020'

b'Our business depends on the sea, and the seafarers that support us as we move cargo around the globe. At this challenging time, we would like to extend our most sincere thanks for the hard work and dedication shown by the DP World family in delivering vital medical supplies to the places that need them most. \n#SeafarersAreKeyWorkers'

b'The security of our clients and their facilities is paramount to DP World, which is why we\xe2\x80\x99ve launched the first autonomous security surveillance boat in the Middle East. With advanced robotic cameras and real-time communications, the boat will safeguard the important industrial and infrastructure assets needed for post-coronavirus recovery.\n\n#Security #Surveillance #Dubai'
b'Did you know that our Borwin Gamma Topside platform in the North Sea can deliver wind energy to 1 million homes? The potential of this vital resource is limitless! \n#GlobalWindDay'

b'Our future requires collective action to the challenges we face. @Expo2020Dubai is already collaborating with people and communities across the globe, supporting and inspiring solutions to some of the most pressing issues of our time. Because together, we can create a brighter future.\n\n#Expo2020 #Dubai'

b'Oceans are the arteries of global trade, and as trade enablers, we know just how important they are for our lives and the planet. Keeping them healthy not only protects global economies, it also means we #ProtectOurHome. \n@WorldOceansDay #WorldOceansDay #OurWorldOurFuture #OceanConservation'

b'On this year\xe2\x80\x99s @UNEP #WorldEnvironmentDay, we\xe2\x80\x99re giving back our valuable marine environments by restating our commitment to blue carbon initiatives. Here is an example of our work in Posorja, where we\xe2\x80\x99ve planted over 140,000 red mangrove seedlings since 2017.  #ForNature #OurWorldOurFuture #Posorja #Ecuador'
b'These waters may look still, but we never are. \n#Vancouver #VancouverPort #SmartTrade'

b'Despite the distance between us this year, we\xe2\x80\x99re more grateful than ever to the growers, makers and traders who have been working tirelessly to bring our celebrations to life. From all of us at DP World, we wish you a peaceful and happy Eid Al-Fitr. \n#EidMubarak'

b'Did you know that when #JebelAli port was inaugurated in 1979, it was one of only three man-made works visible from space? Today, our operations from Terminal 3 have a capacity of 19.3 million TEU per year! \n#SmartTrade #Dubai'

b"As the new title sponsors of the @renaultf1team, we share their love of speed. We're resting our caps for now to respect social distancing, but we\xe2\x80\x99ll be ready to deliver an incredible season, with our @grouperenault partners, when racing starts.\n\n#F1 #Formula1 #RenaultF1 #RenaultF1Team #logistics"

b'Wildlife sanctuaries are a lifeline for tigers like these at Kanha National Park, India. To keep conservation efforts going through Covid-19, we\xe2\x80\x99re donating food material to staff impacted by park closures, to help protect the animals until the tourists return. \n#OurWorldOurFuture #kanhanationalpark #tigerconservation #savethetigers'

b'The Renault DP World F1 Team will enter a British driver line-up for this weekend\xe2\x80\x99s Virtual Spanish Grand Prix as Renault Sport Academy Driver @maxfewtrell is joined by star golfer @ianjamespoulter in black and yellow. Tap the link in our bio to find out more.\n\n#F1 #Formula1 #RenaultF1 #SpanishGrandPrix'

b'@DrydocksWorld has successfully completed construction on a Turret Mooring System, despite challenges posed by the Covid-19 pandemic. \nWe\xe2\x80\x99re putting every necessary measure in place to ensure our yards have the capabilities to keep production on-track, whilst keeping our employees safe, ultimately allowing us to deliver on our project commitments. \n#SmartTrade'
b'Our terminals are never still. If you want a clear shot, you have to move fast!\n\n#SmartTrade #JebelAli #Dubai'

b'Truly game changing projects rely on the secure supply of goods to get them off the ground. That\xe2\x80\x99s why today, on the 30th anniversary of the @nasahubble telescope entering space, we are reminded of how important transporting sensitive, delicate components is for the space industry to push frontiers even further.\n\n#SmartTrade #Hubble30 #HappyBirthdayHubble'
b'On behalf of all of us at DP World, we wish everybody celebrating a safe and peaceful month. #RamadanKareem'

b"From tropical shores to boreal inlets, DP World's terminals are located in some truly special places. As we mark #EarthDay, we'd like to recognise the care each of our local teams show to their environments - such as these young tree planters! \n@EarthDayNetwork #OurWorldOurFuture"
b'DP World Ambassador @ianjamespoulter will compete in the Virtual Chinese GP on Sunday 19th April for the Renault DP World F1 team. Good luck Ian! @renaultf1team\n\n#F1 #Formula1'
b'Sundown at Southampton = striking silhouettes. \n#SmartTrade #Southampton'

b'Our Chairman reflects on the hard work being done to keep trade moving at this challenging time. Read his full blog at the link in our bio.\n\n#Coronavirus #Covid19'

b"Vessels wait in berth at our Caucedo Terminal in the Dominican Republic. Caucedo is located 30 minutes from Santo Domingo, capital of the Dominican Republic, connecting the country's economy to the rest of the world. \n#SmartTrade #DominicanRepublic #Caucedo"

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re working on the proof of concept for BoxBay, our intelligent High Bay Storage system. Swipe to see our progress at Jebel Ali Terminal 4 in Dubai.\n\n#SmartTrade #BoxBay #Dubai #JebelAli'
b'Next train due at platform one: arriving via track, truck and ship! \n#SmartTrade'

b'DP World continues to closely monitor the global impact of COVID-19. We are following the guidance from government and health authorities to ensure we act to protect our customers, employees and the communities where we operate. #Coronavirus #COVID19'
